===Etymology===
Phonetic variant of {{term|seely}}.
From {{etyl|ang}} *{{term||sǣliġ}}, "blessed", (attested only in form {{term|gesælig|ġesǣliġ}}), from {{proto|Germanic|sēlīgaz}}.  Cognate with West Frisian {{term|sillich}}, Dutch {{term|zalig}}, German {{term|selig}}. More at {{l|en|sely}}.

